<topic id="yaml-validation">
  <title>Validating YAML Documents</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>YAML documents<indexterm>Validation</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <section id="section_bx2_jf2_n4b">
      <title>Automatic Validation</title>
      <p id="p_z3g_cgk_54b"><ph keyref="product"/> includes built-in validation engine for YAML
        documents to help you keep them well-formed. YAML documents are validated automatically as
        you type and the validation engine detects syntax errors (such as improper indentation or
        duplicate keys), based on the <xref href="https://yaml.org/spec/1.1/current.html"
          format="html" scope="external">YAML specification</xref>. The built-in validation also
        works on files that consist of multiple YAML documents.</p>
    </section>
    <section id="manually_validate_current_document">
      <title>Manual Validation Actions</title>
      <p id="p_ajg_cgk_54b">To manually validate the currently edited YAML document, use one of the following
        actions:</p>
      <p id="p_bjg_cgk_54b">
        <dl id="dl_oc1_p52_n4b">
          <dlentry id="dlentry_cjg_cgk_54b">
            <dt><uicontrol><image href="../img/Validate16.png" id="image_pc1_p52_n4b"
                />Validate</uicontrol></dt>
            <dd>Available from the <uicontrol><image href="../img/ValidateDrop.png"
                  id="image_qc1_p52_n4b"/>Validation</uicontrol> drop-down menu on the toolbar, the
                <menucascade product="developer editor json">
                <uicontrol>Document</uicontrol>
                <uicontrol>Validate</uicontrol>
              </menucascade><uicontrol product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">YAML</uicontrol>
              menu, or from the <uicontrol>Validate</uicontrol> submenu when invoking the contextual
              menu on one or more YAML documents in the <xref
                href="using-the-project-view.dita#using-the-project-view"><ph
                  product="developer editor json"><uicontrol>Project</uicontrol></ph><ph
                  product="developerEclipse editorEclipse"><uicontrol>Project
                  Explorer</uicontrol></ph> view</xref>. The validation is done based on the <xref
                href="https://yaml.org/spec/1.1/current.html" format="html" scope="external">YAML
                specification</xref>.</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry id="validate-with-action">
            <dt><uicontrol>Validate with</uicontrol></dt>
            <dd>
              <p id="p_xnf_cgk_54b">Available from the <uicontrol><image
                    href="../img/ValidateDrop.png" id="image_n4z_g3b_1jb"/>Validation</uicontrol>
                drop-down menu on the toolbar or the <menucascade product="developer editor json">
                  <uicontrol>Document</uicontrol>
                  <uicontrol>Validate</uicontrol>
                </menucascade><uicontrol product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">YAML</uicontrol>
                menu. This action opens a dialog box that allows you to specify a JSON Schema for
                validating the current YAML document (it also works on files that consist of
                multiple YAML documents).</p>
              <p id="p_znf_cgk_54b">
                <note product="developer editor" id="note_a4f_cgk_54b"><ph> The <uicontrol>Validate
                      with</uicontrol> action does not work for files loaded through a <xref
                      href="custom-protocol-plugin.dita#custom-protocol-plugin">custom protocol
                      plugin</xref> developed independently and added to <ph keyref="product"/>
                    after installation.</ph></note>
              </p>
            </dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry id="dlentry_djg_cgk_54b">
            <dt><uicontrol><image href="../img/WellFormed16.png" id="image_j2c_y52_n4b"/>Check
                Well-Formedness</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol>(<shortcut conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_shift_w_shortcut"
                  product="developer editor"/><shortcut
                  conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/alt_shift_vw_shortcut"
                  product="developerEclipse editorEclipse"/>)</uicontrol></dt>
            <dd>
              <p id="p_ejg_cgk_54b">Available from the <uicontrol><image
                    href="../img/ValidateDrop.png" id="image_k2c_y52_n4b"/>Validation</uicontrol>
                drop-down menu on the toolbar, the <menucascade product="developer editor json">
                  <uicontrol>Document</uicontrol>
                  <uicontrol>Validate</uicontrol>
                </menucascade><uicontrol product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">YAML</uicontrol>
                menu, or from the <uicontrol>Validate</uicontrol> submenu when invoking the
                contextual menu in the <xref
                  href="using-the-project-view.dita#using-the-project-view"><ph
                    product="developer editor json"><uicontrol>Project</uicontrol></ph><ph
                    product="developerEclipse editorEclipse"><uicontrol>Project
                    Explorer</uicontrol></ph> view</xref>. This action checks the document for
                syntax errors to make sure it is well-formed.</p>
            </dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry id="dlentry_b4f_cgk_54b">
            <dt><uicontrol>Validate with Schema</uicontrol></dt>
            <dd>
              <p id="p_c4f_cgk_54b">Available from the <uicontrol>Validate</uicontrol> submenu when
                invoking the contextual menu on one or more YAML documents in the <xref
                  href="using-the-project-view.dita#using-the-project-view"><ph
                    product="developer editor json"><uicontrol>Project</uicontrol></ph><ph
                    product="developerEclipse editorEclipse"><uicontrol>Project
                    Explorer</uicontrol></ph> view</xref>. This action opens a dialog box that
                allows you to specify a JSON Schema to be used for the validation.</p>
            </dd>
          </dlentry>
        </dl>
      </p>
    </section>
    <section id="section_rzp_2h2_n4b">
      <title>Batch Validation</title>
      <p id="p_fjg_cgk_54b">The built-in validation engine can also be used to batch validation
        multiple YAML files at once by selecting multiple files in the <ph
          product="developer editor json"><uicontrol>Project</uicontrol></ph>
        <ph product="developerEclipse editorEclipse"><uicontrol>Project Explorer</uicontrol></ph>
        view, right-click, and select <menucascade>
          <uicontrol>Validate</uicontrol>
          <uicontrol><image href="../img/WellFormed16.png" id="image_qdt_t32_n4b"/>Check
            Well-Formedness</uicontrol>
        </menucascade> or <menucascade>
          <uicontrol>Validate</uicontrol>
          <uicontrol><image href="../img/Validate16.png" id="image_k5n_w32_n4b"
            />Validate</uicontrol>
        </menucascade>. This automatically validates the selected files using the built-in YAML
        validation engine, based on the <xref href="https://yaml.org/spec/1.1/current.html"
          format="html" scope="external">YAML specification</xref>.</p>
    </section>
  </body>
